In today’s world, young people are constantly exposed to challenges against their faith—from social media, school, and even their peers. Apologetics is essential because it equips them to defend, understand, and live out their Catholic faith with confidence.

Many young people leave the Church because they don’t know why they believe what they believe.  Apologetics helps them build a personal relationship with Jesus based on truth.  Apologetics gives them confidence to explain Catholic beliefs clearly and respectfully.  When young Catholics live and defend their faith well, they inspire others to seek truth.

1 Peter 3:15 – "Always be ready to give an answer to anyone who asks you for a reason for your hope."

12 Myths Every Catholic Should Be Able to Answer
